node M1 · M1 · ⟦Celaena Sardothien:M1:b38a09⟧

WHO   — Celaena Sardothien — Adarlan's Assassin · the King's Champion
WHAT  — The protagonist — assassin, prisoner, and Champion; the empire's most feared killer, who hides a reader's heart and a buried grief beneath the legend of her name.
WHERE — M1 · Maas  Framework inputs: Throne of Glass — The Assassin's Blade & book one  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because freedom is the only thing worth killing for and the hardest thing to buy; because a name can be a cage or a weapon; because even a chained killer chooses what she will and will not become.
HOW   — By the blade, the poison, and the years of Arobynn's brutal training; by wit, vanity, and a refusal to break in the mines or the contest; by the ghost-queen's mark and the forbidden Wyrdmarks of an old, outlawed magic.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  My name is Celaena Sardothien — and I will not be afraid.

